<blockquote>
<p>Prime numbers belong to an exclusive world of intellectual conceptions. We speak of those marvellous notions that enjoy simple, elegant description, yet lead to extreme ‚Äî one might say unthinkable ‚Äî complexity in the details. The basic notion of primality can be accessible to a child, yet no human mind harbors anything like a complete picture. <span class="blockquote-attribution">‚ÄîR. Crandall and C. Pomerance</span></p>
